 - gps and such are sticky. Cfb controls everything and running a rogue event sounds like a bad idea
 - my general style is to be very conservative with  public things. This is a personal preference and because i want to minimize the amount of damage control i would possibly have to do. We need more planning, headway, and funding. All of these things are possible but its too early.

Hello and Happy Wednesday,

I hope this email finds you well. We are reaching out in regards to the Magic GP in Tampa for next month.

We have a large gathering of locals in the Orlando area who are huge into Commander (EDH). We were ideally planning to meet up at the event for primarily commander itself, in addition of course go access the various vendors and events there.

From what I'm aware of, I believe commander is viewed as a casual format and there is usually space open for us to freely play. We are happy with this, but we wanted to inquire if we can add our own little signup sheets for pods and the such. 

Ideally we would like to run a signup sheet tournament or two for any EDH players who would like to join. No fees, no qualifications. Again it's a simple sign up sheet and randomized pods to avoid players colluding against others.

We also have set aside various prizes we would like to give out, of course at our own expense. These include various 3d printed trophies and other goodies. If this is unacceptable or youd like to review the prizes. Please let me know.

We would be more then happy to be supervised and directed by your staff. We are simply only interested in providing EDH players with a fun experience. 

Please let me know how to proceed from here, with all the above in mind. 


Thank you,

Kya
